The dataset used in this project consists of Sanskrit text extracted from a PDF document. The content includes basic sentences, facts, and simple informational text used for building a question-answering system.

The PDF is processed to extract raw text, which is then split into smaller meaningful chunks. These chunks form the knowledge base for the Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system.

Each chunk is later converted into vector embeddings and stored in a FAISS index for efficient semantic search during query processing.

This dataset helps the system understand and retrieve relevant Sanskrit context to generate accurate answers.
